title: Davies sharp as Brewers blank Padres
text:
Scott A. Williams , Stevens Point Journal Media 6:09 p.m. CDT October 1, 2015 Unbeaten Amherst football sits at No. 4 nationally among small schools in MaxPreps poll. (Photo: File/Gannett Wisconsin Media) 61 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
AMHERST — There has been no shortage of accolades throughout Wisconsin for the Amherst football team through six weeks of the regular season. 
Now the Falcons (6-0) are grabbing national attention. 
Amherst is ranked No. 4 among small schools in the country in the latest CBS/MaxPreps national football computer rankings released Sept 30. The Falcons stood at No. 18 in the previous poll. 
Trinity Christian Academy of Jacksonville, Fla. is ranked No. 1, followed by Coldwater (Ohio) and Marion Local (Maria Stein, Ohio. Amherst is the only Wisconsin school listed in the top 25. 
Amherst, which sits atop the Central Wisconsin Conference 8 standings, is ranked No. 1 among medium enrollment schools in the latest Associated Press poll. The Falcons also own the top spot in Division 5 in the Wisconsin Football Coaches Association rankings. 
The Falcons, who have outscored teams 321-56, will look to remain unbeaten when they host Manawa on Friday.
